00:33:39,173 --> 00:33:41,566
"And for which we
need feel no obligation."

468
00:33:43,838 --> 00:33:45,243
Is that the end of the play?

469
00:33:46,415 --> 00:33:47,279
Almost.

470
00:33:49,455 --> 00:33:50,642
Let's have some music.

471
00:34:03,340 --> 00:34:05,014
You know, you read that beautifully.

472
00:34:14,328 --> 00:34:15,319
Now you know.

473
00:34:17,468 --> 00:34:18,670
I know it won't do.

474
00:34:23,928 --> 00:34:25,799
Where are you going?
- Out for a walk.

475
00:34:26,340 --> 00:34:28,413
In this rain?
- I like walking in the rain.

476
00:34:29,159 --> 00:34:31,623
So do I. I think I'll go too.
- There is only one slicker.

477
00:35:02,205 --> 00:35:03,615
Why don't you go back?

478
00:35:47,825 --> 00:35:50,770
Kidneys and bacon and cornbread
this morning, Mister Don.

479
00:35:51,746 --> 00:35:52,843
That's fine.

480
00:35:54,613 --> 00:35:58,739
Miss Heath not down yet?
- No. I called her 15 minutes ago.

481
00:36:01,981 --> 00:36:03,565
Mrs Williams, would you mind ..?

482
00:36:06,923 --> 00:36:07,922
Good morning.

483
00:36:09,301 --> 00:36:11,439
Do you like the negligee I
borrowed from Mrs Williams?

484
00:36:14,178 --> 00:36:15,082
It's fine.

485
00:36:22,819 --> 00:36:24,164
Rather cruel, aren't you?

486
00:36:25,229 --> 00:36:26,326
Why do you say that?

487
00:36:26,544 --> 00:36:29,379
Well, you might at least have smiled
at me as I came down the stairs.

488
00:36:30,105 --> 00:36:31,404
Even if it were a lie.

489
00:36:32,801 --> 00:36:34,977
I don't think this is any time to lie.

490
00:36:36,690 --> 00:36:38,735
Or speak the truth or
say anything, in fact.

491
00:36:40,605 --> 00:36:42,302
Could I pour you some coffee?

492
00:36:43,892 --> 00:36:44,759
Joyce.

493
00:36:45,775 --> 00:36:50,350
I hate loose ends .. they tangle
your life, they trip you up.

494
00:36:52,294 --> 00:36:53,221
Yes, Don.

495
00:36:55,453 --> 00:36:56,622
Well, last night ..

496
00:36:57,555 --> 00:37:00,126
I'm sorry I kissed you
and said the things I did.

497
00:37:02,077 --> 00:37:03,874
How very gallant of you to say so.

498
00:37:04,603 --> 00:37:05,895
No, you don't understand.

499
00:37:06,841 --> 00:37:10,417
You see, I'm engaged to someone.
- And you blame me?

500
00:37:11,146 --> 00:37:13,061
No. It was unfair to you too.

501
00:37:14,257 --> 00:37:16,937
You are so very .. fascinating.

502
00:37:17,125 --> 00:37:21,377
I think it was that .. storm and our
nearness that made me lose my senses.

503
00:37:22,985 --> 00:37:25,632
Well, I've got them back this morning,
and I'm asking you to forgive me.

504
00:37:26,521 --> 00:37:29,513
And .. for what I'm saying
now .. if I hurt you.

505
00:37:30,103 --> 00:37:31,035
Hurt me!

506
00:37:34,407 --> 00:37:35,382
You delight me.

507
00:37:35,777 --> 00:37:38,570
You have the most amazing lack
of humor of anyone I've ever known.

508
00:37:40,921 --> 00:37:43,295
I shouldn't laugh at you
should I, but I can't help it.

509
00:37:43,611 --> 00:37:46,472
You were so awkward that I almost
laughed in your face at first.

510
00:37:46,572 --> 00:37:48,715
And then it made me quite
sick to think that anyone ..

511
00:37:48,815 --> 00:37:51,166
Could be stupid enough to be
taken in by a lot of old tricks.

512
00:37:52,085 --> 00:37:53,737
I thought you might at least be amusing.

513
00:37:53,895 --> 00:37:56,767
But you turned out to be dull
and stupid and so afraid.

514
00:37:56,955 --> 00:37:58,105
Well, you needn't be.

515
00:37:58,315 --> 00:38:02,011
I won't hurt your Sunday-School
romance or your oh-so-nice career.

516
00:38:02,372 --> 00:38:05,938
Hurt me? Get out of here
before you give me hysterics!

517
00:38:41,413 --> 00:38:43,711
Sorry friend, but I think you stop here.

518
00:38:44,361 --> 00:38:47,317
It does seem advisable doesn't it.
How soon before it's repaired?

519
00:38:47,542 --> 00:38:49,099
Oh the lumber will be here at noon.

520
00:38:49,199 --> 00:38:51,352
And I think you ought to get
across early this evening.

521
00:38:51,801 --> 00:38:53,561
Too bad you didn't get off last night.

522
00:38:54,515 --> 00:38:55,214
Yeah.

523
00:38:55,883 --> 00:38:58,639
Can one of your men get across and
telephone for me from the other side?

524
00:38:58,790 --> 00:39:01,364
Why, sure.
- Have him call Miss Armitage.

525
00:39:02,077 --> 00:39:04,731
At Austin 9532.

526
00:39:05,719 --> 00:39:08,560
Say that Mr Bellows has been delayed
and can't see her until this evening.

527
00:39:09,522 --> 00:39:12,559
And I'd be very much obliged if you let
me know the minute I can get across.

528
00:39:12,699 --> 00:39:15,665
I'm up at the old Quinn Farm.
- Okay. The first thing.

529
00:39:41,301 --> 00:39:45,065
[ crying sounds ]

530
00:39:47,818 --> 00:39:50,500
[ crying sounds ]

531
00:39:57,519 --> 00:39:58,370
Joyce.

532
00:39:59,114 --> 00:39:59,858
Don!

533
00:40:00,691 --> 00:40:03,704
You did come back.
I was praying you would.

534
00:40:04,726 --> 00:40:06,103
I had to. You see ..

535
00:40:07,137 --> 00:40:09,754
It doesn't matter why.
You did, you had to.

536
00:40:10,558 --> 00:40:12,802
You didn't believe what I
said this morning, did you?

537
00:40:13,858 --> 00:40:14,643
Did you?

538
00:40:15,193 --> 00:40:18,949
I guess I had it coming to me.
- Oh no, no darling. It was a lie.

539
00:40:19,653 --> 00:40:20,988
Well, let's forget about it.

540
00:40:21,138 --> 00:40:23,366
Well, you can forget that. But I
want you to remember this.

541
00:40:23,858 --> 00:40:26,907
I know you belong to somebody else,
and I don't want you, really I don't.

542
00:40:27,883 --> 00:40:29,361
But last night was mine and ..

543
00:40:30,351 --> 00:40:33,866
And I made it ugly this morning. And I
don't want you to think of it that way.

544
00:40:34,278 --> 00:40:35,038
I won't.

545
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:37,487
You will, unless I tell you the truth.

546
00:40:38,351 --> 00:40:40,732
You've seen me drunk and disgusting.

547
00:40:41,236 --> 00:40:44,254
You took me in out of pity.
Well, that hurt my pride.

548
00:40:45,222 --> 00:40:48,353
And because I'm a good deal of
a shrew, I wanted to hurt yours.

549
00:40:49,505 --> 00:40:51,627
I was going to tease you
with all the tricks I knew ..

550
00:40:51,727 --> 00:40:53,222
Until you tried to kiss me, and ..

551
00:40:54,070 --> 00:40:55,537
Then I was to laugh in your face.

552
00:40:56,401 --> 00:40:59,585
I was an actress playing a part.
Well, I played it too well.

553
00:41:01,036 --> 00:41:03,992
But when you took me in your
arms, I didn't want to laugh.

554
00:41:05,055 --> 00:41:06,249
I wanted to cry.

555
00:41:07,566 --> 00:41:09,290
I'm sorry.
- I'm not. I'm glad.

556
00:41:10,416 --> 00:41:11,657
Last night was beautiful.

557
00:41:12,814 --> 00:41:14,181
It will always be beautiful.

558
00:41:15,535 --> 00:41:16,783
And now that it's over.

559
00:41:20,655 --> 00:41:21,808
It's not over, Joyce.

560
00:41:22,658 --> 00:41:25,204
Oh yes, Don. It's got to be over.

561
00:41:26,731 --> 00:41:29,564
Your career is on the verge
of permanent success.

562
00:41:30,137 --> 00:41:32,467
You'll have someone who
can help you. I can't.

563
00:41:33,339 --> 00:41:35,713
I'm the kind of woman
who destroys, not builds.

564
00:41:36,100 --> 00:41:37,733
I'm Joyce Heath, Don.

565
00:41:38,546 --> 00:41:39,693
A Maenad who ..

566
00:41:40,557 --> 00:41:43,433
Doesn't want to dance over the
cliff with a man as fine as you.

567
00:41:45,444 --> 00:41:48,223
Now come on, let's finish up
the rest of the day very fine.

568
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:50,505
I'll get dressed. You go down.

569
00:41:58,624 --> 00:41:59,535
I got it.

570
00:42:05,688 --> 00:42:07,206
No, no. That's not fair.

571
00:42:07,704 --> 00:42:10,483
You must be playing by pinochle rules.
- It's just you're slow, that's all.

572
00:42:10,756 --> 00:42:12,154
Well, no wonder.

573
00:42:12,727 --> 00:42:17,033
These cards are so thick and old I could
be playing with Encyclopedia Britannica.

574
00:42:19,515 --> 00:42:20,961
Wait a minute, wait a minute!

575
00:42:21,703 --> 00:42:23,318
The recipe said it was toffee.

576
00:42:24,738 --> 00:42:26,174
But that's not what we've got.

577
00:42:27,010 --> 00:42:31,047
I'll never get my jaws apart.
I can't bite, I said so.

578
00:42:31,742 --> 00:42:33,911
Pardon me a minute, while
I get out a piece of toffee.

579
00:42:34,193 --> 00:42:36,747
I've lost a couple of molars and
a bicuspid that are sticking to it.

580
00:42:37,329 --> 00:42:39,521
Did you get it?
- Yes, but I think I lost a nail.

581
00:42:40,641 --> 00:42:43,714
Perhaps we should put some sand in that
mess to give it something to hold on to.

582
00:42:45,742 --> 00:42:47,791
I wonder if Mrs Williams
would like some?

583
00:42:48,051 --> 00:42:50,399
It would certainly take the rattle
out her uppers and lowers.

584
00:43:03,186 --> 00:43:04,458
I wish I'd never seen you.

585
00:43:05,411 --> 00:43:07,441
Never kissed you, never
held you in my arms.

586
00:43:08,852 --> 00:43:12,609
Because every time I do,
I hate myself, I hate you.

587
00:43:13,416 --> 00:43:17,026
I can kill every emotion except the
desire to hold you just once more.

588
00:43:18,816 --> 00:43:20,375
[ door knocks ]

589
00:43:26,460 --> 00:43:29,161
You can get across the road now, sir.
- Oh, thank you.

590
00:43:29,334 --> 00:43:32,958
I got the phone call through alright.
- Much obliged. Goodnight.

591
00:43:33,240 --> 00:43:34,132
Goodnight.

592
00:43:40,620 --> 00:43:42,423
You can go now?
- Yes.

593
00:43:43,316 --> 00:43:44,451
Then you must.

594
00:43:45,747 --> 00:43:47,550
Because if you stay,
it will be too late.

595
00:43:48,583 --> 00:43:49,832
I love you.

596
00:43:51,150 --> 00:43:55,012
You may never love me but .. you'll
find you always come back to me.

597
00:43:55,941 --> 00:43:58,928
And each time you return it will
cost you more and more until ..

598
00:43:59,616 --> 00:44:03,545
When you've spent your career,
your ambitions, your dreams.

599
00:44:04,529 --> 00:44:08,332
Oh, I'm bad for people. I don't mean
to be, but I can't help myself.

600
00:44:10,237 --> 00:44:11,964
So I'm being generous to you, Don.

601
00:44:12,396 --> 00:44:15,223
Kind, kinder than I've ever
been to anybody before.

602
00:44:16,470 --> 00:44:20,167
But I can't be much longer .. so go.

603
00:44:21,072 --> 00:44:22,211
Leave me.

604
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:25,382
You can leave me, can't you?

605
00:44:26,850 --> 00:44:27,919
I don't know.

606
00:44:31,497 --> 00:44:32,868
I've got to find out.

607
00:44:42,802 --> 00:44:45,198
Mister Don gone, Miss?
- Yes.

608
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:47,459
He's coming back?

609
00:44:49,845 --> 00:44:51,149
Yes, I think he will.

610
00:44:59,687 --> 00:45:01,114
[ door knocks ]

611
00:45:01,390 --> 00:45:02,410
Yes.

612
00:45:07,230 --> 00:45:08,940
Mr Bellows.
- Uhuh.

613
00:45:09,396 --> 00:45:11,077
Miss Armitage is on the telephone.

614
00:45:14,804 --> 00:45:17,084
Put her on .. no!

615
00:45:19,670 --> 00:45:22,008
Tell her I'm still out of town.
I'll call her when I get back.

616
00:45:24,183 --> 00:45:25,506
Very well, sir.

617
00:45:32,184 --> 00:45:36,913
And Mr Haynes of United Quarries has
called to ask if you have a decision.

618
00:45:38,785 --> 00:45:40,823
Tell him I haven't been
able to make up my mind.

619
00:45:41,125 --> 00:45:44,180
He said he'd have to have an answer
one way or another. Yes or No.

620
00:45:49,743 --> 00:45:53,361
He's right .. it's got to be Yes or No.

621
00:45:55,502 --> 00:45:56,751
Thank you Miss Seals.

622
00:46:07,905 --> 00:46:09,277
[ door knocks ]

623
00:46:09,880 --> 00:46:10,809
Come in.

624
00:46:11,533 --> 00:46:13,712
Mr Bellows, Miss Gail.
- Oh.

625
00:46:14,330 --> 00:46:15,547
Well, show him in, Betty.

626
00:46:15,914 --> 00:46:18,801
And we'll have coffee.
- Van Houtte for Mr Bellows?

627
00:46:19,129 --> 00:46:20,265
That's right.

628
00:46:27,727 --> 00:46:30,921
Well, hello Mr B. About time
you were getting back.

629
00:46:37,984 --> 00:46:40,253
Don .. something has happened?

630
00:46:41,288 --> 00:46:43,220
Yes Gail .. something has happened.

631
00:46:43,812 --> 00:46:46,766
Well, even if it is all for the
worst, it can't be so bad.

632
00:46:47,192 --> 00:46:51,295
Because you've the most best assistant
in the world to help you laugh it off.

633
00:46:51,913 --> 00:46:54,786
Or .. work it out.
Whichever we're going to do.

634
00:46:56,467 --> 00:46:58,805
Gail, it would make me prouder
to have you as my wife ..

635
00:46:58,974 --> 00:47:00,945
Than to have any other
woman in the world.

636
00:47:02,791 --> 00:47:06,323
If I could respect you a little less, it
would all be very simple, but I can't.

637
00:47:07,033 --> 00:47:08,708
So I must ask you a question.

638
00:47:09,178 --> 00:47:11,516
I'm afraid I know the answer already.

639
00:47:12,250 --> 00:47:13,332
What is it, Don?

640
00:47:15,890 --> 00:47:18,379
If we were married, there is one
humiliation you would never know.

641
00:47:18,538 --> 00:47:20,670
That's having me deceive
you with someone else.

642
00:47:21,219 --> 00:47:23,533
I know that.
- But if there were someone else ..

643
00:47:24,144 --> 00:47:27,702
Someone I didn't love, that I'll
never even see again, but who ..

644
00:47:28,630 --> 00:47:32,369
But who had a strange,
exotic fascination for me.

645
00:47:32,670 --> 00:47:34,398
An appeal I couldn't kill.

646
00:47:36,416 --> 00:47:38,065
Would that make any difference to you?

647
00:47:39,133 --> 00:47:40,621
Yes Don, it would.

648
00:47:40,882 --> 00:47:42,944
Whether you ever went to
her or not, wouldn't matter.

649
00:47:43,137 --> 00:47:45,625
But the fact that you'd want to would.

650
00:47:46,451 --> 00:47:49,322
It mightn't make me love
any less .. perhaps more.

651
00:47:50,317 --> 00:47:53,285
But the agony of wondering every time
you kissed me whether you think of her.

652
00:47:53,632 --> 00:47:55,621
The hate and dread I'd have
for that other woman.

653
00:47:55,942 --> 00:47:59,428
And the terrific loneliness of that
little part of you which I wouldn't own.

654
00:48:00,050 --> 00:48:01,459
Would be unendurable.

655
00:48:13,891 --> 00:48:17,411
I can't tell you Don, how much I admire
you for .. for being so honest.

656
00:48:18,023 --> 00:48:20,541
And thank you for coming to say goodbye.

657
00:48:21,902 --> 00:48:23,017
You're a ..

658
00:48:26,298 --> 00:48:27,299
Goodbye.

659
00:48:38,032 --> 00:48:40,741
Mr Bellows gone, Miss Gail?
Is he coming back?

660
00:48:42,281 --> 00:48:43,032
Yes.

661
00:48:44,647 --> 00:48:46,272
Yes, I think he will.

662
00:48:48,525 --> 00:48:53,182
Mr Sheffield, I've come to see you for
some advice on producing a play.

663
00:48:53,482 --> 00:48:55,221
That's something I know nothing about.

664
00:48:55,745 --> 00:49:00,656
An angel is a celestial being after
death, Don. But before .. he's a sucker.

665
00:49:01,613 --> 00:49:04,120
Thanks for the warning.
What I want is an opinion.

666
00:49:04,975 --> 00:49:07,406
Have you ever heard of a
play called "But To Die"?

667
00:49:07,888 --> 00:49:11,396
A magnificent script, which with the
proper lead would make a great play.

668
00:49:11,951 --> 00:49:13,789
However, miscast ..

669
00:49:14,018 --> 00:49:17,395
It would close so fast the third act
curtain would snag in the stage door.

670
00:49:18,203 --> 00:49:19,620
Who do you see in the lead?

671
00:49:20,485 --> 00:49:24,352
There are only two women who could have
played it: Jean Eagles and Joyce Heath.

672
00:49:24,531 --> 00:49:26,735
Eagles is dead .. Heath has disappeared.

673
00:49:27,169 --> 00:49:28,221
So, forget it.

674
00:49:28,472 --> 00:49:31,507
If I made both the script and Miss Heath
available to you, would you produce it?

675
00:49:32,316 --> 00:49:34,596
Mr Bellows, I have great
respect for the script.

676
00:49:34,945 --> 00:49:37,256
And almost a reverence
for Miss Heath's talent.

677
00:49:37,565 --> 00:49:40,345
But I wouldn't hazard
$80,000 to defy a jinx.

678
00:49:40,578 --> 00:49:44,187
Surely an intelligent man like you won't
take any stock in a legend like that?

679
00:49:44,400 --> 00:49:46,723
When you asked $80,000
for a share of it I do.

680
00:49:48,423 --> 00:49:50,175
Suppose I pay the $80,000?

681
00:49:51,743 --> 00:49:54,319
Then I would produce
and direct it myself.

682
00:49:54,939 --> 00:49:56,836
Will you have your lawyer
draw up the contract?

683
00:49:57,762 --> 00:49:58,823
Very well.

684
00:49:59,658 --> 00:50:02,678
By the way .. do you
bite your fingernails?

685
00:50:03,962 --> 00:50:05,709
No.
- You will.

686
00:50:15,299 --> 00:50:18,191
[ dog barking ]

687
00:50:50,760 --> 00:50:53,682
You did come.
- You knew I would.

688
00:50:56,730 --> 00:50:57,889
Yes, I knew.

689
00:51:06,815 --> 00:51:09,313
Let's go inside, I've only got a
minute. I've got to go right back.

690
00:51:09,810 --> 00:51:10,824
Tonight?
- Yeah.

691
00:51:20,275 --> 00:51:21,740
Darling.
- Joyce.

692
00:51:23,974 --> 00:51:25,176
I want to talk to you.

693
00:51:33,363 --> 00:51:34,330
Now listen ..

694
00:51:34,819 --> 00:51:38,206
You and I are both artists. I deal
in permanence, things that last.

695
00:51:38,591 --> 00:51:42,087
You in emotions, moments, things
that flame and burn and leave ashes.

696
00:51:42,793 --> 00:51:44,568
So we're not the same. I know that.

697
00:51:45,723 --> 00:51:48,164
But is there any consistency in
the way you feel towards me?

698
00:51:49,319 --> 00:51:50,887
Couldn't we ask questions afterwards?

699
00:51:51,253 --> 00:51:53,928
No .. I can't build without plans.

700
00:51:54,707 --> 00:51:57,586
Answer me, Joyce. Is there any
consistency in your feelings towards me?

701
00:52:00,120 --> 00:52:03,661
Tonight I love you so much that nothing
else matters. A love you couldn't kill.

702
00:52:04,749 --> 00:52:05,982
But that's tonight.

703
00:52:07,249 --> 00:52:09,747
Tomorrow should be the
same. I want it to be.

704
00:52:10,780 --> 00:52:13,954
But I've betrayed so often by
tomorrows, I don't dare promise that.

705
00:52:15,352 --> 00:52:17,347
It's the only honest answer
I can give you darling.

706
00:52:18,179 --> 00:52:21,599
That's a gentleman's answer, Joyce.
- I guess I'm not lady enough to lie.

707
00:52:23,600 --> 00:52:24,949
No, I don't think you would.

708
00:52:26,614 --> 00:52:27,935
I broke my engagement.

709
00:52:29,083 --> 00:52:30,790
Why?
- Because of us.

710
00:52:32,229 --> 00:52:34,846
Well, what about her?
- Now, let's leave her out of it.

711
00:52:35,925 --> 00:52:39,255
I know that she's stronger than us,
as if she weren't, I wouldn't be here.

712
00:52:40,345 --> 00:52:41,633
And I'm glad I'm weaker.

713
00:52:42,598 --> 00:52:45,265
You are too, aren't you? Say you are.
- No, I'm not.

714
00:52:46,269 --> 00:52:49,274
I'm here.
- That's all I care about.

715
00:52:49,678 --> 00:52:51,715
There are other things
that are important to me.

716
00:52:52,631 --> 00:52:54,235
First of all, your career.

717
00:52:54,941 --> 00:52:56,939
Why should you concern
yourself about that?

718
00:52:57,211 --> 00:52:59,594
Because you don't belong in
the audience, but on the stage.

719
00:53:00,216 --> 00:53:03,030
Your emotion, your restlessness,
have beauty and poetry there.

720
00:53:03,631 --> 00:53:06,201
Off the stage they'd be brutal.
They would ruin us both.

721
00:53:06,690 --> 00:53:11,132
I hope that in the theater you'll find
enough release to be content with me.

722
00:53:11,816 --> 00:53:14,145
Why should I find
contentment? I don't want it.

723
00:53:14,464 --> 00:53:17,574
Well I do. I want you,
and I want peace, too.

724
00:53:18,137 --> 00:53:21,003
They wouldn't let me inside the theater.
They'd be afraid it would fall down.

725
00:53:21,820 --> 00:53:25,245
You start rehearsing "But To Die" for
George Sheffield on Monday morning.

726
00:53:26,203 --> 00:53:27,095
What?

727
00:53:28,243 --> 00:53:29,238
Me?

728
00:53:30,459 --> 00:53:31,736
But To Die?

729
00:53:32,459 --> 00:53:34,412
Oh you're mad.
Sheffield wouldn't risk it.

730
00:53:34,975 --> 00:53:36,750
You get the script from him tomorrow.

731
00:53:37,613 --> 00:53:40,710
Don .. did you put your money in it?
- Yes.

732
00:53:41,067 --> 00:53:44,663
Oh you fool .. you crazy fool!
Something will happen.

733
00:53:45,200 --> 00:53:47,085
I've told you a million
times I'm a jinx.

734
00:53:47,555 --> 00:53:49,801
You are no such thing.
You're a great actress.

735
00:53:50,324 --> 00:53:53,966
I'm so sure, I'm risking the money that's
to realize the one ambition I ever had.

736
00:53:54,830 --> 00:53:56,515
You're going to be better than you were.

737
00:53:56,615 --> 00:53:59,564
If I'm going to marry Joyce Heath,
it's got to be the <i>real</i> Joyce Heath.

738
00:54:07,605 --> 00:54:09,417
Marry?
- Yes.

739
00:54:09,737 --> 00:54:12,449
I can't compromise, and I
won't sneak and apologize.

740
00:54:13,285 --> 00:54:16,055
I'm playing you a game,
but I'm playing it for keeps.

741
00:54:18,891 --> 00:54:19,943
What's the matter?

742
00:54:23,023 --> 00:54:24,506
Nothing, only ..

743
00:54:25,987 --> 00:54:28,170
Well, it's all happened
so quickly you know.

744
00:54:28,504 --> 00:54:33,114
Being told about doing the play, and
your wanting to marry me. You see ..

745
00:54:34,692 --> 00:54:36,649
Well, it would ruin your career, Don.

746
00:54:37,048 --> 00:54:39,278
Your society and
theater .. they don't mix.

747
00:54:39,508 --> 00:54:40,827
There is still marriage.

748
00:54:41,983 --> 00:54:45,351
Yes, I know but .. let's not
talk about it just now.

749
00:54:46,490 --> 00:54:47,539
Speak, Don.

750
00:54:48,168 --> 00:54:50,818
Going on the stage for the first
time in two years to play for you ..

751
00:54:51,107 --> 00:54:52,650
Your career and mine.

752
00:54:53,154 --> 00:54:55,889
Our lives, our success depending
on one performance.

753
00:54:56,895 --> 00:54:59,158
When the lights go out
and that curtain goes up ..

754
00:54:59,402 --> 00:55:01,242
Oh Don, that is being alive.

755
00:55:01,665 --> 00:55:04,135
I love you, I love you for
bringing me back to life.

756
00:55:04,876 --> 00:55:06,980
Are you going back to town tonight?
- Right away.

757
00:55:07,308 --> 00:55:08,895
Well, I'm going with you.
- Why?

758
00:55:09,139 --> 00:55:11,036
To leave two years behind.

759
00:55:13,799 --> 00:55:15,029
Faster!

760
00:55:17,720 --> 00:55:18,737
Faster.

761
00:55:33,980 --> 00:55:37,267
So that's all it's been to you, Charles.
Just a ship-board romance.

762
00:55:37,521 --> 00:55:38,966
Oh, no it wasn't.
- Oh yes.

763
00:55:39,689 --> 00:55:44,171
Just a man telling a woman that the
moon is not half as lovely as she is.

764
00:55:44,969 --> 00:55:47,235
Swearing devotion eternal as the tides.

765
00:55:47,530 --> 00:55:50,643
Sweeping the girl off her
feet .. all to be forgotten.

766
00:55:52,418 --> 00:55:54,140
Well, that isn't what it meant to me.

767
00:55:54,661 --> 00:55:56,737
No Charles. It has meant far more.

768
00:55:57,695 --> 00:56:00,652
Your every word, your every
kiss, your every caress.

769
00:56:01,571 --> 00:56:02,563
I've treasured.

770
00:56:03,637 --> 00:56:06,819
Because I've always pretended they
belong to the man I really love.

771
00:56:10,705 --> 00:56:12,385
Now that's something for you to forget.

772
00:56:13,304 --> 00:56:14,280
If you can.

773
00:56:15,586 --> 00:56:16,484
That's fine.

774
00:56:16,987 --> 00:56:18,241
How about it, Miss Heath?

775
00:56:18,341 --> 00:56:20,058
Too tired to go through
that scene again?

776
00:56:20,272 --> 00:56:21,333
No, I'd love to.

777
00:56:22,407 --> 00:56:26,094
I'm sorry .. I've got to
beg off .. I'm all in.

778
00:56:26,909 --> 00:56:28,639
You've got too much vitality for me.

779
00:56:29,012 --> 00:56:31,227
And for me too .. we'll call it off.

780
00:56:31,536 --> 00:56:34,457
No rehearsal tomorrow. And we'll run
through it again at 10 o'clock Monday.

781
00:56:34,729 --> 00:56:36,823
I don't like to work on the
day of the night we open.

782
00:56:37,001 --> 00:56:39,355
But there's some things
I must change .. that's all.

783
00:56:40,013 --> 00:56:41,025
Alright boys ..

784
00:56:44,622 --> 00:56:47,354
Give me a cigarette.
- Sure .. what do you think?

785
00:56:47,513 --> 00:56:49,669
I've spent a fortune and
misspent a life in the theater.

786
00:56:50,029 --> 00:56:52,292
But this is the only time on
the eve of a dress rehearsal ..

787
00:56:52,442 --> 00:56:54,179
I've had nerve enough
to say I had a hit.

788
00:56:54,310 --> 00:56:55,487
You're pretty positive.

789
00:56:55,587 --> 00:56:57,880
So positive that I'll buy your
piece of it for a $100,000.

790
00:56:58,094 --> 00:57:02,570
Oh no. Here's one angel who isn't afraid
to tread. I'm just as certain as you are.

791
00:57:03,782 --> 00:57:04,955
Isn't she magnificent?

792
00:57:05,209 --> 00:57:07,702
Even in rehearsal, the greatest
performance I've ever seen.

793
00:57:08,184 --> 00:57:12,107
With the stimulus of an audience, Monday
will make her immortal in the theater.

794
00:57:12,691 --> 00:57:13,793
What about that jinx?

795
00:57:13,893 --> 00:57:16,644
The devil himself couldn't
jinx a talent like that.

796
00:57:16,870 --> 00:57:17,668
Like it?

797
00:57:17,846 --> 00:57:20,587
Oh, it's alright, I guess.
Needs a lot of work, though.

798
00:57:20,926 --> 00:57:24,174
You know darling, if I could get away to
the country and go over this on Sunday.

799
00:57:24,333 --> 00:57:26,840
I think I'd get a better perspective.
Would you run me down tonight?

800
00:57:26,981 --> 00:57:29,852
Certainly, not a bad idea.
We'd better get under way.

801
00:57:29,952 --> 00:57:31,907
I must stop by the apartment
to get my clothes.

802
00:57:32,007 --> 00:57:33,172
Alright .. goodnight.

803
00:57:33,384 --> 00:57:36,111
Goodnight, and keep her out of
the poison ivy and the fresh air.

804
00:57:36,426 --> 00:57:38,253
I don't want her to open in a whisper.

805
00:57:43,954 --> 00:57:45,030
Darling.

806
00:57:48,331 --> 00:57:49,906
We can't go on like this.

807
00:57:50,389 --> 00:57:52,451
I could .. forever.

808
00:57:52,608 --> 00:57:54,583
Don't be evasive Joyce.
You know what I mean.

809
00:57:56,042 --> 00:57:57,178
Getting married?

810
00:57:58,244 --> 00:57:59,026
Well ..

811
00:57:59,896 --> 00:58:01,503
Of course, sometime darling.

812
00:58:01,946 --> 00:58:04,931
But right now .. there
is the show to think of.

813
00:58:05,401 --> 00:58:07,520
You always find some reason
to change the subject.

814
00:58:08,054 --> 00:58:09,962
Tell me the truth. Why
are you putting me off?

815
00:58:10,517 --> 00:58:12,120
Don't be so intense, Don.

816
00:58:12,856 --> 00:58:16,206
You know I love you and that there
is no-one else .. isn't that enough?

817
00:58:16,356 --> 00:58:19,076
No, it's not enough. What's the matter,
are you afraid to marry me?

818
00:58:19,690 --> 00:58:22,072
Afraid? Why should I be?

819
00:58:22,312 --> 00:58:25,286
I don't know, unless you think marriage
will make me harder to get rid of.

820
00:58:25,452 --> 00:58:27,031
Oh don't say that Don. Don't.

821
00:58:27,623 --> 00:58:30,921
That night when you asked me, I told
you I couldn't promise you tomorrows.

822
00:58:31,620 --> 00:58:35,145
I can now. I love you enough
to give them all to you.

823
00:58:35,806 --> 00:58:37,136
At least as many as you want.

824
00:58:37,248 --> 00:58:39,569
Then we'll be married right after
the opening on Monday night.

825
00:58:41,304 --> 00:58:42,138
So soon?

826
00:58:42,461 --> 00:58:44,707
If you meant what you said just
now, it wouldn't seem soon.

827
00:58:44,895 --> 00:58:47,592
Well, it's not that Don, only ..
- Only what?

828
00:58:47,939 --> 00:58:51,135
Well .. well marriage seems to make
such an issue out of everything.

829
00:58:51,743 --> 00:58:53,287
Why can't we wait a while?
- No.

830
00:58:53,465 --> 00:58:56,034
I'm not going to trail around after
you like a stage-door Johnny.

831
00:58:56,179 --> 00:58:58,818
And make a sap out of myself
waiting for you to get out of a mood.

832
00:58:59,231 --> 00:59:01,766
I want you .. but I'm through begging.

833
00:59:03,498 --> 00:59:05,029
It's either Monday night or never.

834
00:59:06,996 --> 00:59:09,968
Well of course, darling .. alright.

835
00:59:10,391 --> 00:59:12,798
I'll marry you Monday,
right after the show.

836
00:59:13,415 --> 00:59:15,396
We'll go down to the
park for one glorious day ..

837
00:59:15,574 --> 00:59:18,513
And I hope it rains and washes
the bridge and the roads away.

838
00:59:18,813 --> 00:59:22,530
So we'll be marooned forever. Put your
arms around me, and tell me you love me.

839
00:59:23,046 --> 00:59:25,864
Look here Joyce, you're almost
hysterical. What's the matter?

840
00:59:26,015 --> 00:59:29,497
Oh nothing. Excitement, nerves.
Worrying about the show.

841
00:59:29,724 --> 00:59:33,066
Listen, I've changed my mind.
I'm very tired from rehearsing.

842
00:59:33,330 --> 00:59:35,892
I'd rather go to the country alone.
Would you lend me your car?

843
00:59:36,391 --> 00:59:39,508
Well, sure if you want, but I'd hate
to have you driving alone at night.

844
00:59:39,705 --> 00:59:43,930
Oh, don't be silly. Now be a good boy,
and go now or you'll see me cry.

845
00:59:46,560 --> 00:59:49,124
Hey, what's the matter?
- Nothing I tell you, but stage fright.

846
00:59:49,274 --> 00:59:51,293
Go home now, there is
always a taxi out front.

847
00:59:51,621 --> 00:59:55,565
I see that the old Southern hospitality
and the artistic temperament don't mix.

848
00:59:55,838 --> 00:59:59,488
Goodnight, drive carefully and
leave the jitters down there.

849
01:00:18,409 --> 01:00:21,828
I got your bag all packed for you, honey.
- Well, put it down and get out of here!

850
01:00:22,260 --> 01:00:23,122
Yes, ma'am.

851
01:01:29,252 --> 01:01:30,154
Joyce.

852
01:01:31,330 --> 01:01:33,591
I hoped you'd come
like this so many times.

853
01:01:35,056 --> 01:01:38,250
And you have, haven't you?
- Yes .. on business.

854
01:01:39,272 --> 01:01:40,135
Come in.

855
01:01:46,933 --> 01:01:48,802
I rather hate to have
you see my quarters.

856
01:01:48,980 --> 01:01:52,013
Spare yourself any embarrassment.
I didn't come here out of curiosity.

857
01:01:52,498 --> 01:01:54,117
You'll find this one more comfortable.

858
01:01:54,217 --> 01:01:56,614
I shan't be here long enough
to find this one uncomfortable.

859
01:01:59,700 --> 01:02:02,029
Cigarette?
- No thank you.

860
01:02:18,773 --> 01:02:21,244
You still hate me, don't you?
- No Gordon, I don't.

861
01:02:22,079 --> 01:02:25,590
There is an element of respect and
hate. All I feel for you is contempt.

862
01:02:27,460 --> 01:02:28,793
You are very fortunate.

863
01:02:29,413 --> 01:02:32,810
Contempt is much easier to carry in your
heart than a love you can't destroy.

864
01:02:36,054 --> 01:02:37,617
You do love me, don't you Gordon?

865
01:02:39,306 --> 01:02:42,180
When a man ruins his life for something,
it's liable to be pretty real.

866
01:02:44,639 --> 01:02:47,605
I'm a bookkeeper now, Joyce.
In a company that I used to own.

867
01:02:49,325 --> 01:02:50,939
The worst of it is, I can't hate you.

868
01:02:51,710 --> 01:02:53,485
I don't suppose you can understand that.

869
01:02:53,983 --> 01:02:56,085
I never could before. I do now.

870
01:02:57,563 --> 01:03:00,329
You see, I lost somebody
that way too, Gordon.

871
01:03:01,259 --> 01:03:02,386
Heaven help you.

872
01:03:02,793 --> 01:03:05,362
Heaven help me .. if you won't.

873
01:03:07,691 --> 01:03:10,299
You want me to divorce you?
- Oh yes, Gordon.

874
01:03:11,322 --> 01:03:14,047
I've told you time and
time again, that I won't.

875
01:03:14,687 --> 01:03:18,016
You are my wife .. something
will never be to any other man.

876
01:03:19,303 --> 01:03:22,773
Being your husband is the only thing
I've got left and I <i>won't</i> lose it!

877
01:03:25,099 --> 01:03:26,974
You'll be my wife until the day I die.

878
01:03:27,841 --> 01:03:29,221
Then I'll divorce you.

879
01:03:30,289 --> 01:03:31,632
You can't, Joyce.

880
01:03:32,477 --> 01:03:34,429
You haven't any grounds.
You never will have.

881
01:03:43,039 --> 01:03:47,014
Gordon .. I know I've ruined your
happiness, but don't ruin mine.

882
01:03:47,437 --> 01:03:49,470
If it's revenge you want,
I'll give it to you.

883
01:03:49,658 --> 01:03:52,584
I'll beg, I'll crawl, I'll do
anything. Anything!

884
01:03:52,922 --> 01:03:55,489
Gordon .. Gordon, look at me.

885
01:03:55,946 --> 01:03:57,767
If you want to humiliate me,
you know how.

886
01:03:57,936 --> 01:04:00,716
But set me free, give me my
one chance of happiness.

887
01:04:01,283 --> 01:04:04,342
Please Gordon .. please, please!

888
01:04:06,530 --> 01:04:09,261
Oh you cheap, petty bookkeeper, you.

889
01:04:09,839 --> 01:04:14,475
Every time I think of those sticky hands
of yours touching me, it makes me sick.

890
01:04:14,852 --> 01:04:17,867
"Sick" do you hear? You're
everything that's repulsive to me.

891
01:04:18,299 --> 01:04:22,175
Your wife? I've never been a wife
to you, you poor, simpering fool.

892
01:04:22,480 --> 01:04:25,755
If you had any pride, if you were a
man, instead of a drooling milksop.

893
01:04:26,085 --> 01:04:28,949
You'd throw me out and be ashamed
to admit that you ever married me!

894
01:04:33,556 --> 01:04:35,938
I guess I'm better protected
against you than I used to be.

895
01:04:40,686 --> 01:04:42,837
Neither that, nor what
you said seemed to hurt.

896
01:04:43,723 --> 01:04:44,644
Gordon.

897
01:04:46,193 --> 01:04:48,456
Gordon .. you <i>can't</i> still love me.

898
01:04:49,189 --> 01:04:50,625
When you know how I feel.

899
01:04:51,743 --> 01:04:52,860
Yes, I do.

900
01:04:53,367 --> 01:04:54,851
And .. you ..

901
01:04:55,517 --> 01:04:57,536
And I won't divorce you .. no.

902
01:05:15,936 --> 01:05:17,119
Gordon.

903
01:05:18,407 --> 01:05:20,919
Gordon, I guess we're
ordained never to be happy.

904
01:05:21,529 --> 01:05:24,512
So perhaps it would be better to
make the best of what we have.

905
01:05:25,228 --> 01:05:27,423
To try and find contentment together.

906
01:05:28,444 --> 01:05:31,179
That's all I'd ask, Joyce .. ever.

907
01:05:32,317 --> 01:05:34,441
I'm going down to the
country over the weekend.

908
01:05:35,468 --> 01:05:37,070
Come along if you like.

909
01:05:38,337 --> 01:05:39,628
May I, Joyce?

910
01:05:40,321 --> 01:05:41,421
May I?

911
01:05:52,685 --> 01:05:53,821
Gordon.

912
01:05:54,330 --> 01:05:56,771
Would nothing in the world
induce you to divorce me?

913
01:05:57,869 --> 01:05:58,770
Nothing.

914
01:05:59,131 --> 01:06:01,446
Not even to save your life?
- No.

915
01:06:02,347 --> 01:06:04,530
Then we're going to settle
this thing once and for all.

916
01:06:04,917 --> 01:06:06,889
If I can't have him, I'd rather be dead.

917
01:06:07,347 --> 01:06:10,141
It's going to be your life or mine.
- Good!

918
01:06:11,093 --> 01:06:14,145
We're coming to a tree in the
middle of the road. We're taking it.

919
01:06:14,320 --> 01:06:17,995
If you're killed, I'll be free. If I'm
killed, it really doesn't matter.

920
01:06:18,288 --> 01:06:21,094
If we both die .. good riddance.
- Good!

921
01:06:21,493 --> 01:06:24,404
You've taken everything else but
my life. I don't want that without you.

922
01:06:24,627 --> 01:06:26,332
Go ahead .. crash it!

923
01:06:37,609 --> 01:06:40,860
Well, I heard a crash,
and I came a running.

924
01:06:41,388 --> 01:06:44,642
And then I saw Miss Heath with
this fellow. And that's all I know.

925
01:06:44,991 --> 01:06:47,737
Oh, I wonder how badly
the little thing is hurt.

926
01:06:47,913 --> 01:06:49,610
But how do you know it was Joyce Heath?

927
01:06:49,710 --> 01:06:52,268
Well, she's been staying
at Mr Bellows' farm.

928
01:06:52,655 --> 01:06:54,827
I ought to know. I'm his housekeeper.

929
01:06:55,226 --> 01:06:57,440
Mr Bellows? You mean
Donald Bellows the architect?

930
01:06:57,596 --> 01:07:01,669
That's who I mean. And if you want to
know more you'd better ask him yourself.

931
01:07:01,927 --> 01:07:03,610
He should be here by now. I phoned.

932
01:07:03,817 --> 01:07:06,454
Yeah thanks. It might
be a good idea to ask.

933
01:07:12,731 --> 01:07:15,687
Listen, I need First Aid.
I'm a reporter, I got a lead.

934
01:07:15,875 --> 01:07:19,200
I don't want to use the pay-phone
because of the other reporters, so ..

