Mrs Heath.

1026
01:13:38,213 --> 01:13:41,406
I was just in to see your husband.
He's been inquiring about you.

1027
01:13:42,781 --> 01:13:44,133
Oh, my husband.

1028
01:13:46,659 --> 01:13:47,928
Oh yes, my husband.

1029
01:13:50,475 --> 01:13:53,938
I must get up today.
- But you can't. It's much too soon.

1030
01:13:55,673 --> 01:13:58,552
I must get up .. I've got
some debts to pay.

1031
01:14:01,146 --> 01:14:05,457
Of course you know, to reopen a play
that's failed, and make a success of it.

1032
01:14:05,665 --> 01:14:08,124
Is next to impossible.
- The play wasn't a failure.

1033
01:14:08,612 --> 01:14:10,313
The only failure was mine to appear.

1034
01:14:10,923 --> 01:14:14,377
I can make that play a success.
- You are quite confident?

1035
01:14:15,725 --> 01:14:17,231
More than confident, I'm positive.

1036
01:14:18,307 --> 01:14:19,362
Why?

1037
01:14:19,751 --> 01:14:21,475
Four very distinct reasons.

1038
01:14:22,004 --> 01:14:24,865
Any one of them so important to
me that it makes failure impossible.

1039
01:14:26,077 --> 01:14:28,483
First, I'm the only actress
suited to that part.

1040
01:14:29,704 --> 01:14:31,723
Second, Don must get his money back.

1041
01:14:33,154 --> 01:14:36,112
Third, I have a husband who's
injured for life because of me.

1042
01:14:37,333 --> 01:14:38,957
I must support him.

1043
01:14:39,539 --> 01:14:41,244
And last but most important.

1044
01:14:41,995 --> 01:14:45,624
I found out how to break
my jinx .. by paying my debts.

1045
01:14:48,392 --> 01:14:50,763
Are you strong enough to
start rehearsing Monday?

1046
01:14:52,441 --> 01:14:53,426
Yes.

1047
01:14:55,849 --> 01:14:57,248
I've got to be.

1048
01:14:57,953 --> 01:15:00,785
